    <text>
        <body>
            <pb n="1" facs="1911Jul28a.jpg"/>
            <opener>
                <handShift new="#h2"/>
                <dateline>
                    <name>Hulls Cove Maine</name>
                    <date when="1911-07-28">July 28" 1911</date>
                </dateline>
                <salute>My dear <persName ref="/sites/default/files/1523819227/tei/Annotations.xml#pers_edith_abbott">Miss Abbott</persName></salute>
            </opener>
            <p>I am very grateful for 
                the many kind things you 
                are doing for me and I 
                am fairly ashamed to ask 
                another&#8212;but I do very 
                much want the three or four 
                brown colored pamphlets 
                issued by <persName>Prof Henderson’s</persName> <!-- Add ref when annotation file is done CH -->
                society. Is it called the 
                Society of Moral Prophylactics 
                and Social Hygiene, or something 
                of the kind.</p>
            <p>I do not clearly know where</p>
            <pb n="2" facs="1911Jul28b.jpg"/>
            <pb n="3" facs="1911Jul28c.jpg"/>
            <p>my copies are, <choice><orig>altho</orig><reg>although</reg></choice> I think 
                on the top shelf of the open 
                book case near the door of 
                my sitting room. If they 
                aren’t there will you have 
                them send me here, other 
                copies for the U. of C.?</p>
            <p>I shall always be sorry 
                that you did<unclear reason="illegible" cert="high" resp="#eb">n't</unclear> come up 
                from <unclear reason="illegible" cert="low" resp="#eb">Barton</unclear> to see this 
                beautiful spot. <unclear reason="illegible" cert="high" resp="#eb">Do try 
                to</unclear> have your <persName>sister</persName> and Dr 
                <persName>Miegs</persName> stop here on their 
                way to Montreal. It would</p>
            <pb n="4" facs="1911Jul28d.jpg"/>
            <pb n="5" facs="1911Jul28e.jpg"/>
            <p>not be at the least 
                impossible for them to do it, 
                I think as far as S.S.<!--Was this person's name S.S. McClure/do we have an annotation for them?--> went.</p>
            <p><persName>McClure</persName> is hurrying me 
                to the first “reading” of my 
                <unclear reason="illegible" cert="low" resp="#eb">stuff</unclear>. I have quite 
                enjoyed <unclear reason="illegible" cert="low" resp="#eb">writing</unclear> it, <choice><orig>altho</orig><reg>although</reg></choice> the 
                <unclear reason="illegible" cert="high" resp="#eb">subject</unclear> is <unclear reason="illegible" cert="high" resp="#eb">grisly</unclear>. I have 
                tried to hide it, under the 
                title "A New Conscience and 
                an Ancient Evil". With 
                affectionate feelings to Miss 
                <persName>Breckinridge</persName>,</p>
            <closer>
                <salute> Always devotedly yours </salute>
                <signed>
                    <persName>Jane Addams.</persName>
                </signed>
            </closer>
            
            <pb n="6" facs="1911Jul28f.jpg"/>
